I"<p>Most <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/neurotransmitters-and-hormones-are-means-of-biochemical-signaling">hormones</a> are either secreted by various brain cells in certain <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/triune-brain-model-classifies-brain-regions-through-evolutionary-lens">regions</a>, or are secreted as a cascade effect of <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/neurotransmitters-and-hormones-are-means-of-biochemical-signaling">hormones</a> secreted by such cells. <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/second-brain-buffer-is-like-short-term-memory">The hypocampus</a> and other <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/brains-are-like-monkeys-with-supercomputers">subcortical</a> regions are particularly involved in hormone secretion.</p>
